From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: aiopquic <noreply@aiopquic>
Date: Tue, 27 May 2026 12:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] h3zero: forward picoquic_callback_stream_released to path
 callback

Patch 0003 added picoquic_callback_stream_released as the canonical
per-stream retirement signal — fires once per stream when picoquic
has fully retired it (pure receivers on FIN/RESET; senders/bidi when
all sent data ACKed). For raw QUIC apps with their own callback_fn
this works directly.

For H3/WT apps, picoquic invokes h3zero_callback as cnx->callback_fn
and h3zero owns each stream's h3zero_stream_ctx_t. Without this
forward, h3zero silently ignores stream_released and apps registered
via path callbacks never learn mid-session that a stream is retired —
they can only clean per-stream state at session close (when h3zero
empties its tree). For workloads with high mid-session stream churn
this means per-stream app state accumulates for the full session
lifetime.

Forwarding fires picohttp_callback_free per-stream as picoquic
retires it. h3zero then deletes its own stream_ctx (mirrors the
session-close path's picosplay_empty_tree). The stream is gone from
picoquic at this point so subsequent picoquic callbacks for it
cannot fire — no use-after-free risk in the path callback's cleanup.
---
diff --git a/picohttp/h3zero_common.c b/picohttp/h3zero_common.c
index 1234567..89abcde 100644
--- a/picohttp/h3zero_common.c
+++ b/picohttp/h3zero_common.c
@@ -1965,6 +1965,25 @@ int h3zero_callback(picoquic_cnx_t* cnx,
 			* after the limits for unidir streams are known */
 			ret = h3zero_protocol_init_safe(cnx, ctx);
 			break;
+		case picoquic_callback_stream_released:
+			/* picoquic patch 0003 fires this per-stream when fully
+			 * retired. Forward to the registered path callback as
+			 * picohttp_callback_free so the app can release per-
+			 * stream context mid-session, then delete h3zero's own
+			 * stream_ctx. Without this, apps can only clean at
+			 * session close (picosplay_empty_tree). */
+			if (stream_ctx == NULL) {
+				stream_ctx = h3zero_find_stream(ctx, stream_id);
+			}
+			if (stream_ctx != NULL) {
+				if (stream_ctx->path_callback != NULL) {
+					(void)stream_ctx->path_callback(cnx, NULL, 0,
+						picohttp_callback_free,
+						stream_ctx, stream_ctx->path_callback_ctx);
+				}
+				h3zero_delete_stream(cnx, ctx, stream_ctx);
+			}
+			break;
 		default:
 			/* unexpected -- just ignore. */
 			break;
